cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.COMM, cs.SY, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on improving the performance of LTE-U/LAA and WiFi networks under cross-technology coexistence scenarios, which falls under the scope of networking and internet architecture. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper proposes a new communication scheme that leverages the time-frequency resource grid of an OFDM transmitter, which involves information theory concepts such as channel coding and modulation. 
3. cs.COMM (Communications and Networking) - The paper deals with improving the communication between LTE-U/LAA and WiFi networks, which falls under the scope of communications and networking. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper proposes a new system for cross-technology communication, which involves system design and control. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper evaluates the performance of the proposed scheme in terms of data rate, which is a multimedia-related metric.
